A highlight of all the best things that happened to me in 2022:

• a brunch on a tree pod, hanging from the top of the canopy jungle in Thailand 🌳
• a dinner 50 meters high in the sky in Dubai 🍽
• flying in a hot air balloon over the Dubai desert 🐪
• experiencing the longest zip-rider in the world 🌎
• whale watching in Alaska 🐋
• going on our first cruise trip 🚢
• swimming with mantas & whale sharks in Maldives 🐳
• eating breakfast with alpacas 🦙
• finding two of the most beautiful world’s beaches in Thailand (Maya Bay) and Bahamas (Rose Island) 🏝
• met the whitest sand in Barbados 🇧🇧
• catamaran trip with the best group of people in Bahamas ⛵️
• waterfalls exploring in Jamaica 💦
• sand-boarding in Saudi 🏄‍♀️
• experiencing the sickest Heaven&Hell Spa in the Dolomites 🧖‍♀️
• cycling on water at Lake Garda 🚲
• sleeping on the edge in South Tyrol 🏔
• taking a scenic flight over Maldives ✈️
• Sicily+Tropea road-trip 🚗
• trip with an old-timer through Germany
• eating our way through Venice 🛶
• swimming at historical thermal baths in Budapest 🛁

These experiences are eveythingggg and more and I will carry them with me forever 🤍 thank you #2022 🔝 I hope #2023 is half as good to us as you were 🙏🏼

MEXICAN RIVIERA CRUISE 7 DAY ITINERARY👇🏻 save for later!

Day 1 - Day one is spent at sea which means a lot of time to do fun things on-board the NCL Bliss. Our day started with a morning wave from a whale and sea lions jumping out the water. We had a delightful breakfast at the Savor, then adrenaline packed day driving go-karts and trying out the water-slides. For lunch we watched a super pod of dolphins swimming directly towards our ship - this was probably the highlight of the trip for me! They came so close to the ship, I cried a little. 🐬🥲

Day 2 - My favourite destination of the trip was also our first stop - Cabo San Lucas, known as the jewel of the Baja Peninsula. Approaching the famous El Arch was already a spectacle of itself. Few moments later we saw 2 whales jumping out the water. 🐳 Coming to Cabo I would definitely recommend booking a whale tour! For us unfortunately it was already sold out, so we visited the famous El Arco and enjoyed our day relaxing on the secluded shores of Lover’s beach instead - it was equally amazing! Cabo is known as the haven for sea lions so we saw plenty. Other great activities here include parasailing over pristine waters and snorkel tours. We came back to the boat for a coffee break and enjoyed the view through the observation lounge. We wrapped our day drinking champagne on our balcony, enjoying the spectacular El Arco view, followed by a dinner at Cagney’s steakhouse.

Day 3 - This morning we made it all the way to Puerto Vallarta. We booked the Ultimate 4x4 RZR Expedition to explore the scenic countryside, swim in the waterfall, and sample local tequilas. I recommend wearing old clothes and shoes for this one because you will get very dusty! Another big bucket-list place in Puerto Vallarta for us includes Mexico’s Hidden Beach at Marieta Islands. 🏝️

MEDITERRANEAN CRUISE 9 DAY ITINERARY with @norwegiancruiseline 👇🏼 save for later!

Day 1 - Lisbon was our embarkation port and as we wanted to explore Portugal’s hilly, coastal capital city we arrived a day early 🇵🇹 We boarded Norwegian Getaway ship in the afternoon, unpacked our things and watched us sail away from our balcony — although we had seen various views of the iconic Ponte 25 de Abril bridge, it seemed so different from this perspective. We kicked off the cruise with an exciting and flavorful dining experience at Teppanyaki 🍽️

Day 2 - Entire day is spent AT SEA which means a lot of time to explore as much of the ship as possible and see all the ship has to offer. After all, we don’t want to realise certain features of the ship on the last day of the cruise. The highlight for us was when we passed the Straits of Gibraltar during sunset, seeing two continents at once - Europe on the left and Africa on the right. 🌊

Day 3 - After a very restful night we made it to our 1st port: GRANADA, SPAIN 🇪🇸 We booked a kayak excursion through @norwegiancruiseline to explore the dramatic Cliffs of Maro Cerro Gordo, stunning coastal caves and secluded beaches. As we sailed away, we watched several pods of dolphins swimming by the ship, surfing the waves 🐬 It was a moment for the books! We wrapped up our beautiful day with a romantic dinner at French restaurant Le Bistro - it was magnifique. 🥂✨

Day 4 - We fuelled up in the morning at the Savor (my favourite breakfast restaurant on board the Norwegian Getaway) before our adventure packed day in IBIZA, SPAIN 🇪🇸 We visited a remote part of the island, called Atlantis (aka. Capturing galaxy with the Galaxy S23 Ultra - the camera capabilities are just so mind-blowing and Santorini looks even more beautiful after the night falls 🌌 @samsungslovenija

Below is my step-by-step guide how to nail your astro shots 📸

• Firstly, I recommend bringing a tripod with you and if you’re shooting in a complete dark also bring a headlamp💡
• Download Expert Raw App on your Samsung
• Put your phone on a tripod 
• Open Expert Raw App
• Make a few test shots so you nail your composition first
• Go to settings and make sure they are are set to RAW + enable special photo options
• For best possible results - choose 10 minutes duration
• I use wide lens and set focus to 0.9 for the sharpest stars
• Tap the shutter button and wait for 10 minutes to see the result

This is obvious, but make sure to shoot when the sky is clear! ✨

Moreover, see below if you want to shoot a hyperlapse video (stars moving 💫):

• Open a Camera App
• Select Hyperlapse
• Select UHD
• Set recording speed to 300x
• Tap on Stars trail option in the right bottom corner
• Click the shutter
• Leave for at least an hour!

Now it’s time to go test it yourself! 🌃
